<subSubSection id="C352C4B24352FFB2CCF2FB28FA3EFA71" pageId="9" pageNumber="219" type="key">
<keyStep id="30BC8F9C4352FFB2CCF2FB28FA3FFA8C" pageId="9" pageNumber="219">
<paragraph id="8BF797394352FFB2CCF2FB28FA3EFAA8" blockId="9.[136,1452,1272,1496]" box="[136,1451,1272,1294]" pageId="9" pageNumber="219">
<keyLead id="30B9340C4352FFB2CCF2FB28FA3EFAA8" box="[136,1451,1272,1294]" pageId="9" pageNumber="219">1. Racemes ebracteate, rarely lowermost 1 or 2 flowers bracteate ........................................................................................................2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF797394352FFB2CCF2FAC7FA3FFA8C" blockId="9.[136,1452,1272,1496]" box="[136,1450,1301,1323]" pageId="9" pageNumber="219">
<keyLead id="30B9340C4352FFB2CCF2FAC7FA3FFA8C" box="[136,1450,1301,1323]" pageId="9" pageNumber="219">
– Racemes bracteate throughout or rarely only along lowermost third......................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C48ECBA4352FFB2C969FAC7FA3FFA8C" authorityName="H. Hara" authorityYear="1974" baseAuthorityName="de Candolle" baseAuthorityYear="1821" box="[1299,1450,1301,1323]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Rorippa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="9" pageNumber="219" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="benghalensis">
<emphasis id="B93C4B2B4352FFB2C969FAC7FA3FFA8C" box="[1299,1450,1301,1323]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="219">R. benghalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30BC8F9C4352FFB2CCF2FAE3FA3EFAC2" pageId="9" pageNumber="219">
<paragraph id="8BF797394352FFB2CCF2FAE3FA3EFAE1" blockId="9.[136,1452,1272,1496]" box="[136,1451,1330,1352]" pageId="9" pageNumber="219">
<keyLead id="30B9340C4352FFB2CCF2FAE3FA3EFAE1" box="[136,1451,1330,1352]" pageId="9" pageNumber="219">
2. Seeds biseriate; fruit often 
<quantity id="4CB03ADC4352FFB2CDAFFAE3FDBBFAEE" box="[469,558,1330,1352]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="219" unit="cm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="1.0">1–2.5 cm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4CB03ADC4352FFB2CE11FAE3FD59FAEE" box="[619,716,1330,1352]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="219" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.0">1–1.5 mm</quantity>
wide ................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C48ECBA4352FFB2C92EFAE2FA3EFAE1" authorityName="Hiern" authorityYear="1896" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1763" box="[1364,1451,1330,1352]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Rorippa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="9" pageNumber="219" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis id="B93C4B2B4352FFB2C92EFAE2FA3EFAE1" box="[1364,1451,1330,1352]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="219">R. indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF797394352FFB2CCF2FA9EFA3EFAC2" blockId="9.[136,1452,1272,1496]" box="[136,1451,1359,1381]" pageId="9" pageNumber="219">
<keyLead id="30B9340C4352FFB2CCF2FA9EFA3EFAC2" box="[136,1451,1359,1381]" pageId="9" pageNumber="219">
– Seeds uniseriate; fruit often 
<quantity id="4CB03ADC4352FFB2CD9BFA9EFDAFFAC2" box="[481,570,1359,1381]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="219" unit="cm" value="2.75" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="2.0">2–3.5 cm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4CB03ADC4352FFB2CE0DFA9EFD4DFAC2" box="[631,728,1359,1381]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="219" unit="mm" value="0.75" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.5">0.5–1 mm</quantity>
wide.............................................................................................................3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30BC8F9C4352FFB2CCF2FABDFA3EFA71" pageId="9" pageNumber="219">
<paragraph id="8BF797394352FFB2CCF2FABDFA3EFA3B" blockId="9.[136,1452,1272,1496]" pageId="9" pageNumber="219">
<keyLead id="30B9340C4352FFB2CCF2FABDFA3EFA3B" pageId="9" pageNumber="219">
3. Petals mostly absent, if present, often shorter than sepals, 
<quantity id="4CB03ADC4352FFB2CE8FFABDFCF2FA27" box="[757,871,1388,1410]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="219" unit="mm" value="2.0" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2.5 mm</quantity>
long, 0.2–0.7(–1) mm wide; fruit straight, (1.5–) 2.5–3.5(–4) cm long, 0.7–0.9 (–1) mm wide ............................................................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C48ECBA4352FFB2C923FA58FA3EFA3B" baseAuthorityName="Al-Shehbaz" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[1369,1451,1416,1438]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Rorippa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="9" pageNumber="219" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dubia">
<emphasis id="B93C4B2B4352FFB2C923FA58FA3EFA3B" box="[1369,1451,1416,1438]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="219">R. dubia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF797394352FFB2CCF2FA77FA3EFA71" blockId="9.[136,1452,1272,1496]" pageId="9" pageNumber="219">
<keyLead id="30B9340C4352FFB2CCF2FA77FA3EFA71" pageId="9" pageNumber="219">
– Petals present, petals longer than sepals or equal to the sepals, (1.5–)2–3(–3.5) mm long, 
<quantity id="4CB03ADC4352FFB2C848FA74FB14FA1D" box="[1074,1153,1445,1467]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="219" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2 mm</quantity>
wide; fruit often curved, (1.5–)2–3(–3.5) cm long, 0.5–0.7 (–8) mm wide ..................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C48ECBA4352FFB2C8AEFA12FA3EFA71" authorityName="Zheng &amp; Yu &amp; Xing &amp; Han" authorityYear="2021" box="[1236,1451,1474,1496]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Rorippa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="9" pageNumber="219" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hengduanshanensis">
<emphasis id="B93C4B2B4352FFB2C8AEFA12FA3EFA71" box="[1236,1451,1474,1496]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="219">R. hengduanshanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
